$ cmd.exe - command extension

When → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] is started, *command extensions* are enabled or disabled by giving either the
`/e:on` or `/e:off` → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe#cmd-exe-options[option].

In a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files[batch file], command extensions can be enabled with → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/setlocal[`setlocal enableExtension`].

Command extensions affect the following commands and features
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/assoc
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/call
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/cd
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/color
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/del
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/endlocal
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/for
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/ftype
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/goto
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/if
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/mkdir
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/popd
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/prompt
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/pushd
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/set
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/setlocal
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/shift
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/start
  • The → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/variables/PROMPT[`%PROMPT%`] variable recognizes `$M` and `$+`.



